cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes an efficient client-to-client streaming approach for video-on-demand (VoD) applications, which involves unicast communication among clients. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2) cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with streaming videos, which is a multimedia application. 
3) cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed approach involves cooperative proxy and client chaining scheme for streaming videos, which can be considered as a distributed computing problem. 
4) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of prefix caching scheme to minimize the request-service delay for the user, which can be considered as a data structure and algorithm problem. 
5) cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The client-to-client streaming approach involves utilizing the client to client bandwidth, which can be considered as a social and information network problem.
